The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 World Briefs

 Saddam comedy 

 Baghdad, March 15 (Reuters): A combative Saddam Hussein formally took the stand at his trial today and urged Iraqis to fight invaders, prompting the judge to bar reporters from the court the former president denounced as a comedy. 

 I call on the people to start resisting the invaders instead of killing each other, Saddam told the chamber in Baghdads heavily fortified Green Zone. The toppled leader warned Iraqis to avoid civil war in a country he ruled with an iron fist for three decades. 

 France offer 

 Paris (Reuters): French President Jacques Chirac urged unions and students on Wednesday to take up his governments offer of talks on a youth jobs law that has sparked mass protests around the country and rattled his Prime Minister. 

 UN rights 

 United Nations (Reuters): The UN General Assembly on Wednesday created a new UN human rights body, despite objections from the US. Applause greeted the announcement of the 170 to 4 vote. 




